                {
                    "name": "Primal Dragons",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Magma dragons belong to a caste of dragons known as primal dragons\u2014massive scaled beings that hail from the Elemental Planes and the Plane of Shadow. Other primal dragons include power-hungry brine dragons from the Plane of Water, whimsical cloud dragons from the Plane of Air, haughty crystal dragons from the Plane of Earth, and sadistic umbral dragons from the Shadow Plane.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Pathfinder #148: Fires of the Haunted City",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq0204d?Pathfinder-Adventure-Path-148-Fires-of-the-Haunted-City"
                        },
                        "page": 80
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Magma dragons are considered unpredictable and brash by other dragons. They lair within volcanically active mountains and throughout the steaming, stony borderlands between the Plane of Fire and the Plane of Earth.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Pathfinder #148: Fires of the Haunted City",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq0204d?Pathfinder-Adventure-Path-148-Fires-of-the-Haunted-City"
                },
                "page": 80
            }
        }
